cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image reconstruction, denoising, inpainting, and super-resolution, which are all topics related to computer vision. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an algorithm for learning an analysis operator from training images, which involves optimization and linear algebra techniques commonly used in machine learning. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of sparse representations in image reconstruction, which is a topic related to information theory. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image reconstruction and denoising, which are topics related to multimedia processing. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes an optimization algorithm based on lp-norm minimization and conjugate gradient method, which are topics related to numerical analysis.
